data.title: The Olympic Athlete: What it Takes to Get to the Games
data.meta_description: “The Olympic Athlete: What it Takes to Get to the Games”, was held April 2012. Speakers included Carl Georgevski, a three-time Olympic coach and current head coach of the Blues track and field program; Professor Gretchen Kerr, a sport psychology expert and advisor to competitive athletes in gymnastics, swimming and skating; and Professor Greg Wells, host of Gemini Award-winning Superbodies and sport physiologist to world champion kayaker Adam van Koeverden.
